# No Barrel Files in src/lib

Do not add or keep barrel `index.ts` files in `src/lib/constants/` or `src/lib/utils/`. They add indirection, obscure where exports come from, and can pull in unused code.

Import directly from the concrete module:

```ts
import { MOBILE_BREAKPOINT } from "@/lib/constants/breakpoints";
import { SUPPORT_FAQS } from "@/lib/constants/support";
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils/cn";
import { getPackageId } from "@/lib/utils/get-package-id";
```

- Constants: use `@/lib/constants/<file>` (e.g. `breakpoints`, `landing`, `plans`, `subscription`, `support`).
- Utils: use `@/lib/utils/<file>` (e.g. `cn`, `get-matches`, `get-error-message`, `get-package-id`).
